# MongoDB Atlas Configuration
# Replace <username>, <password>, and <cluster-url> with your actual MongoDB Atlas credentials
# Example: mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster0.xxxxx.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@<cluster-url>/?retryWrites=true&w=majority
DATABASE_NAME=banking_system
SECRET_KEY=banking-secret-key-change-in-production-12345
FLASK_ENV=development

# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Go to https://cloud.mongodb.com and sign up/login (FREE!)
# 2. Create a FREE cluster (M0 Sandbox - FREE forever)
# 3. Create a database user (Database Access -> Add New Database User)
# 4. Whitelist your IP (Network Access -> Add IP Address -> 0.0.0.0/0 for all IPs)
# 5. Get connection string (Database -> Connect -> Connect your application)
# 6. Replace <username>, <password>, and <cluster-url> in MONGODB_URI above
